  <bp:ProteinReference rdf:ID="ProteinReference6">
    <bp:organism rdf:resource="#BioSource1" />
    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">UniProt:P29622 SERPINA4</bp:name>
    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">SERPINA4</bp:name>
    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">KST</bp:name>
    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">PI4</bp:name>
    <bp:xref rdf:resource="#UnificationXref63" />
    <bp:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">FUNCTION Inhibits human amidolytic and kininogenase activities of tissue kallikrein. Inhibition is achieved by formation of an equimolar, heat- and SDS-stable complex between the inhibitor and the enzyme, and generation of a small C-terminal fragment of the inhibitor due to cleavage at the reactive site by tissue kallikrein.SUBUNIT Monomer and some homodimers.TISSUE SPECIFICITY Expressed by the liver and secreted in plasma.PTM The N-terminus is blocked.MISCELLANEOUS Heparin blocks kallistatin's complex formation with tissue kallikrein and abolishes its inhibitory effect on tissue kallikrein's activity.SIMILARITY Belongs to the serpin family.</bp:comment>
  </bp:ProteinReference>
