    <bp:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">FUNCTION Co-chaperone that binds to numerous proteins and promotes their interaction with Hsp70 and Hsp90.SUBUNIT Self-associates. Forms complexes with Hsp70 and Hsp90. Interacts with CDC37, FKBP4, PPID and STIP1.TISSUE SPECIFICITY Expressed in brain, heart, kidney, liver, placenta and skeletal muscle.SIMILARITY Belongs to the CDC37 family.</bp:comment>
