    <bp:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">FUNCTION Tetranectin binds to plasminogen and to isolated kringle 4. May be involved in the packaging of molecules destined for exocytosis. Plays a role in retinal function (PubMed:35331648).SUBUNIT Homotrimer.TISSUE SPECIFICITY Found in plasma.</bp:comment>
  </bp:ProteinReference>
