    <bp:xref rdf:resource="#UnificationXref84" />
    <bp:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">FUNCTION May have a specific function in the mechanism or regulation of T-cell cytolytic activity.FUNCTION (Microbial infection) Plays a role during influenza virus infection in lungs cells ex vivo. Acts at the level of virus entering host cytoplasm from late endosome.TISSUE SPECIFICITY Expressed predominantly in natural killer cells, and in cytotoxic T cells.SIMILARITY Belongs to the peptidase C1 family.</bp:comment>
  </bp:ProteinReference>
