    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">UniProt:O00292 LEFTY2</bp:name>
    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">LEFTY2</bp:name>
    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">EBAF</bp:name>
    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">LEFTA</bp:name>
    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">LEFTYA</bp:name>
    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">TGFB4</bp:name>
    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">PSEC0024</bp:name>
    <bp:xref rdf:resource="#UnificationXref230" />
    <bp:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">FUNCTION Required for left-right (L-R) asymmetry determination of organ systems in mammals. May play a role in endometrial bleeding.TISSUE SPECIFICITY Mesenchymal cells of the endometrial stroma.DEVELOPMENTAL STAGE Transiently expressed before and during menstrual bleeding.PTM The processing of the protein may also occur at the second R-X-X-R site located at AA 132-135. Processing appears to be regulated in a cell-type specific manner.SIMILARITY Belongs to the TGF-beta family.</bp:comment>
  </bp:ProteinReference>
