    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">AAP</bp:name>
    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">PLI</bp:name>
    <bp:xref rdf:resource="#UnificationXref301" />
    <bp:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">FUNCTION Serine protease inhibitor. The major targets of this inhibitor are plasmin and trypsin, but it also inactivates matriptase-3/TMPRSS7 and chymotrypsin.SUBUNIT Forms protease inhibiting heterodimer with TMPRSS7.TISSUE SPECIFICITY Expressed by the liver and secreted in plasma.PTM Proteolytically cleaved at Pro-39 by both the prolyl endopeptidase FAP form and antiplasmin-cleaving enzyme FAP soluble form to generate mature alpha-2-antiplasmin.SIMILARITY Belongs to the serpin family.</bp:comment>
  </bp:ProteinReference>
