  <bp:ProteinReference rdf:ID="ProteinReference62">
    <bp:organism rdf:resource="#BioSource1" />
    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">UniProt:P62328 TMSB4X</bp:name>
    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">TMSB4X</bp:name>
    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">TB4X</bp:name>
    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">THYB4</bp:name>
    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">TMSB4</bp:name>
    <bp:xref rdf:resource="#UnificationXref331" />
    <bp:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">FUNCTION Plays an important role in the organization of the cytoskeleton (PubMed:1999398, PubMed:10848969). Binds to and sequesters actin monomers (G actin) and therefore inhibits actin polymerization (PubMed:1999398, PubMed:10848969).SUBUNIT Identified in a complex composed of ACTA1, COBL, GSN AND TMSB4X (PubMed:23009842). Interacts with SERPINB1 (By similarity).TISSUE SPECIFICITY Expressed in several hemopoietic cell lines and lymphoid malignant cells. Decreased levels in myeloma cells.INDUCTION By alpha interferons. Decreased levels in THP-1 cells after treatment with recombinant interferon-lambda.SIMILARITY Belongs to the thymosin beta family.</bp:comment>
  </bp:ProteinReference>
