    <bp:xref rdf:resource="#UnificationXref614" />
    <bp:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">FUNCTION NADH-cytochrome b5 reductases are involved in desaturation and elongation of fatty acids, cholesterol biosynthesis, drug metabolism, and, in erythrocyte, methemoglobin reduction.TISSUE SPECIFICITY Widely expressed.SIMILARITY Belongs to the flavoprotein pyridine nucleotide cytochrome reductase family.</bp:comment>
  </bp:ProteinReference>
