    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">SYTL4</bp:name>
    <bp:xref rdf:resource="#UnificationXref626" />
    <bp:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">FUNCTION Modulates exocytosis of dense-core granules and secretion of hormones in the pancreas and the pituitary. Interacts with vesicles containing negatively charged phospholipids in a Ca(2+)-independent manner (By similarity).SUBUNIT Part of a ternary complex containing STX1A and RAB27A. Can bind both dominant negative and dominant active mutants of RAB27A. Binds STXBP1, RAB3A, RAB8A and RAB27B. Interacts with MYO5A (By similarity).</bp:comment>
  </bp:ProteinReference>
