  <bp:ProteinReference rdf:ID="ProteinReference125">
    <bp:organism rdf:resource="#BioSource1" />
    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">UniProt:O43852 CALU</bp:name>
    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">CALU</bp:name>
    <bp:xref rdf:resource="#UnificationXref806" />
    <bp:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">FUNCTION Involved in regulation of vitamin K-dependent carboxylation of multiple N-terminal glutamate residues. Seems to inhibit gamma-carboxylase GGCX. Binds 7 calcium ions with a low affinity (By similarity).SUBUNIT Interacts with GGCX.TISSUE SPECIFICITY Ubiquitously expressed. Expressed at high levels in heart, placenta and skeletal muscle, at lower levels in lung, kidney and pancreas and at very low levels in brain and liver.SIMILARITY Belongs to the CREC family.</bp:comment>
  </bp:ProteinReference>
