    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">SB139</bp:name>
    <bp:xref rdf:resource="#UnificationXref825" />
    <bp:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">FUNCTION Saccharide- and LPS-binding protein with possible roles in pathogen sensing and endotoxin neutralization. Ligand-binding specificity relates to the length of the oligosaccharides, with preference for chitotetraose (in vitro).SUBUNIT Interacts with STAB1.TISSUE SPECIFICITY Expressed in cells of monocytic, T, B and epithelial origin.INDUCTION Up-regulated by IL4/interleukin-4 and dexamethasone in the macrophages. Up-regulated by glucocorticoid.SIMILARITY Belongs to the glycosyl hydrolase 18 family.</bp:comment>
  </bp:ProteinReference>
